Any invocation of pskgen fails with a syntax error.

    % pskgen --help
    syntax error at /usr/local/sbin/pskgen line 67, near "do Getopts("
    Execution of /usr/local/sbin/pskgen aborted due to compilation errors.

The port also reports

    pkg: POST-INSTALL script failed

on install because pskgen is invoked from the plist.

    % uname -a
    FreeBSD build.saltant.net 10.3-STABLE FreeBSD 10.3-STABLE #3 r301173: Wed Jun  1 18:48:58 EDT 2016     root@build.saltant.net:/usr/obj/usr/src/sys/CUSTOM  amd64
    % pkg info -xo perl5 racoon2
    perl5-5.20.3_13                lang/perl5.20
    racoon2-20100526a_10           security/racoon2
    % head -68 /usr/local/sbin/pskgen | tail -7
    if ($] > 5.014002) {
            use Getopt::Std;
            getopts('rs:o:di:he:d');
    } else {
            require 'getopts.pl';
            do Getopts('rs:o:di:he:d');
    }
